trans-unit.source: Wraps an XSD <xref uid="langword_csharp_QName" name="QName" href=""></xref> type.
For more information about XSD data types, see the "XML Data Types Reference" in the MSDN Library at [http://msdn.microsoft.com/library](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library).
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Runtime.Remoting.Metadata.W3cXsd2001.SoapQName"></xref> class.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Runtime.Remoting.Metadata.W3cXsd2001.SoapQName"></xref> class with the local part of a qualified name.
A <xref:System.String> that contains the local part of a qualified name.
Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Runtime.Remoting.Metadata.W3cXsd2001.SoapQName"></xref> class with the namespace alias and the local part of a qualified name.
A <xref:System.String> that contains the namespace alias of a qualified name.
A <xref:System.String> that contains the local part of a qualified name.

Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Runtime.Remoting.Metadata.W3cXsd2001.SoapQName"></xref> class with the namespace alias, the local part of a qualified name, and the namespace that is referenced by the alias.
A <xref:System.String> that contains the namespace alias of a qualified name.
A <xref:System.String> that contains the local part of a qualified name.
A <xref:System.String> that contains the namespace that is referenced by `key`.
Returns the XML Schema definition language (XSD) of the current SOAP type.
A <xref:System.String> indicating the XSD of the current SOAP type.
Gets or sets the namespace alias of a qualified name.
A <xref:System.String> that contains the namespace alias of a qualified name.
Gets or sets the name portion of a qualified name.
A <xref:System.String> that contains the name portion of a qualified name.
Gets or sets the namespace that is referenced by <xref:System.Runtime.Remoting.Metadata.W3cXsd2001.SoapQName.Key*>.
A <xref:System.String> that contains the namespace that is referenced by <xref:System.Runtime.Remoting.Metadata.W3cXsd2001.SoapQName.Key*>.
Converts the specified <xref:System.String> into a <xref href="System.Runtime.Remoting.Metadata.W3cXsd2001.SoapQName"></xref> object.
The <xref:System.String> to convert.
A object that is obtained from value.
Returns the qualified name as a <xref:System.String>.
A <xref:System.String> in the format " <xref:System.Runtime.Remoting.Metadata.W3cXsd2001.SoapQName.Key*> : <xref:System.Runtime.Remoting.Metadata.W3cXsd2001.SoapQName.Name*> ".
If <xref:System.Runtime.Remoting.Metadata.W3cXsd2001.SoapQName.Key*> is not specified, this method returns <xref:System.Runtime.Remoting.Metadata.W3cXsd2001.SoapQName.Name*>.
Gets the XML Schema definition language (XSD) of the current SOAP type.
A <xref:System.String> that indicates the XSD of the current SOAP type.
